The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: Finance minister P. Chidambaram apprising Prime Minister Manmohan Singh of a slowdown in key infrastructure sectors such as coal, steel and construction has said bottlenecks to production in these areas must be removed. In a recent letter to the Prime Minister, Chidambaram said, Our assessment is that there has been a slowdown in key infrastructure sectors. While there is no evidence of a slow down in investment, bottlenecks to enhanced production need to be addressed and removed.

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: TVS Motor today claimed that it had delivered a copy of its patent revocation application to Bajaj Auto. TVS counsel Lakshmi Kumaran said although the revocation application was filed in August, it takes time for the appellate board to send notices and, therefore, TVS informed Bajaj about the application itself.

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: DaimlerChrysler is planning to enter into co-operation with Jalandhar-based Sutlej Motors for building bus bodies. The companies plan to build bus bodies on Mercedes-Benz chassis manufactured by DaimlerChrysler India.

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: IFCI would appoint a due diligence adviser to provide suggestions for inducting a strategic investor who could pick up to 26 per cent stake in it.

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: The coal ministry is finalising modalities to grant Mini Ratna status to Central Coalfields Ltd, a subsidiary of Coal India Ltd.

 Geneva, Sept. 4: Trading nations today launched a three-week drive to break a long-standing deadlock in key agricultural negotiations at the World Trade Organisation, officials said.

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: Sharp rise in prices of crude oil in the international market and rupee appreciation have affected Indias oil import growth, which touched the lowest level of 5.33 per cent in the past five years.




